revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-04-23 22:31:31.000000000', 'files': ['etc/barbican/barbican-api-paste.ini'], 'message': "Removing signing_dir directive from config

The signing_dir directive defined in barbican-api-paste.ini explicitly
stores Keystone's signing certificates in a known /tmp directory. This
could be exploited by populating the directory with bogus certificates,
potentially allowing a malicious user to generate valid tokens.

Added comment explaining signing_dir, and a reasonable
(commented) default.

Change-Id: I15fda6863e888e3881694ab47a836eee2fb578ee
Closes-Bug: #1446406
"}]
commit_message:
Removing signing_dir directive from config

The signing_dir directive defined in barbican-api-paste.ini explicitly
stores Keystone's signing certificates in a known /tmp directory. This
could be exploited by populating the directory with bogus certificates,
potentially allowing a malicious user to generate valid tokens.

Added comment explaining signing_dir, and a reasonable
(commented) default.

Change-Id: I15fda6863e888e3881694ab47a836eee2fb578ee
Closes-Bug: #1446406

subject: Use a watch that isn't affected by time going backwards
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-04-22 18:45:40.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'shade/task_manager.py'], 'message': "Use a watch that isn't affected by time going backwards

On versions of python that have monotonic time the usage
of the oslo.utils stop watch will ensure that that code is
used vs using time.time which can go backwards if ntpd or
other system time is altered during running tasks.

Change-Id: Ia50a5582e931c80da12a15aa9f8597b44ae57597
"}]
commit_message:
Use a watch that isn't affected by time going backwards

On versions of python that have monotonic time the usage
of the oslo.utils stop watch will ensure that that code is
used vs using time.time which can go backwards if ntpd or
other system time is altered during running tasks.

Change-Id: Ia50a5582e931c80da12a15aa9f8597b44ae57597

commit_message:
Add option to install Heat's test image

Add HEAT_TEST_IMAGE option (defaulting to false), enabling which
will add a default image used in Heat's integration tests to Glance.

commit_message:
Support Unicode in requirements file

Currently, if there's a Unicode char in requirements, pbr fails. There's
no need to fail, we can use io.open() to handle that instead.

Change-Id: I15e0ff87e72e9890781fc1627804f2811bf2ecb2

commit_message:
Create Consistency Group from CG Snapshot CLI

This patch addressed the following:
* Added a new CLI to support creating a CG from a CG snapshot.

cinder consisgroup-create-from-src [--cgsnapshot <cgsnapshot>]
                                   [--name <name>]
                                   [--description <description>]

API patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/145952/

Partial-Implements: blueprint consistency-groups-kilo-update

commit_message:
Remove upgraded kernel check for new clusters

- In 6.1 we don't ship packages on ISO and we can't
get kernel version which is to be installed on new nodes.
So check was only left for old clusters

commit_message:
Remove project association before removing endpoint group

Since `project_endpoint_group` has a foreign key reference with `endpoint_group`
thus, if we want to remove endpoint_group we need to remove associated
`project_endpoint_group` at first.

The testcase provided can pass even without code changing only beacuse SQLITE
didn't enforce foreign key constraint by default, so endpoint group with project
association can be deleted (needn't delete project association at first)
successfully.

Closes-Bug: #1443765
bp ondelete-cascade

Change-Id: Id685948373ffb37467f336172a085b91c982cbc7

commit_message:
Isolate injection tests

The first injection test was always tainted by the previous tests since
the dependencies where not cleared before the test run. This change
makes sure that there are no dependencies registered at the start of
each test.

commit_message:
Use gearman to limit token flush to one host

Currently keystone will run one flush per controller, which leads to
excessive churn and rollbacks, which can be disruptive to service.

This uses gearman to have the least-busy controller run the flush. It
still may run into problems if the flush takes longer than four hours
but the cleanup script _should_ be exitting before that time is up.

Note that this will also require changes in the Heat templates to pass
the control Virtual IP in as a gearman.address

Change-Id: Iee7d7541b691f45d0961f2112baebba452c8aecf
Partial-Bug: #141882

commit_message:
Remove pysqlite test-requirement dependency

pysqlite is no longer needed with py27 and definitely note needed
in py34. Eliminate this as a test-requirement. This has the added
benefit of eliminating one of the very few libaries that are blocking
keystone from being python3.4 compatible.

Change-Id: I63d5f0473fdfd91b559b47e7dd9ab4c4307a7c03

commit_message:
L3 DB: Defer port DB subnet lookups

_populate_subnets_for_ports was being called multiple
times for different interface types during the get_routers
process.

This patch eliminates those extra queries by deferring the
subnet information population until after all of the interfaces
have been looked up. Includes a function rename as well to
indicate that a function is only used internally.

Change-Id: Ib46f685d72eb61ecbaa2869e28fb173cd6d49552
Partial-bug: #1445412

commit_message:
Add release pinning to galera roles

As both Ubuntu and the MariaDB repositories carry packages with the same
names, apt package pinning is required to ensure that the packages we install
come from the right repository. This patch adds a pinning preference file to
ensure that the packages we install come from the MariaDB repository.

Due to the OpenStack CI images having conflicting packages installed in the
base image, this patch also includes the removal of these packages during the
AIO bootstrap to ensure that the deployment succeeds.

For environments where the same two packages are installed on the hosts prior
to the deployment of os-ansible-deployment, they would need to ensure that the
packages are removed first. This has been seen in environments where
monitoring tooling has installed the packages as a dependancy.

Also, the swift installation process requires access to the Ubuntu backports
repository to install the liberasurecode1 and liberasurecode-dev packages. In
the hpcloud environments used in OpenStack-CI the backport repository is not
implemented, so we need to ensure that it's there if it hasn't already been
configured. This patch does that as part of the AIO bootstrap process.

Finally, this patch also updates the global requirements and the sha's for all
openstack branches that we're pinned to.

Closes-Bug: #1446772
Closes-Bug: #1448152
Change-Id: I5ad0b9010e49832c4f866c0b141e1c035d5f9268
(cherry picked from commit 886fe01edb01b9f21e3576f50711738687b236d9)

commit_message:
Add the function of deleting alarm history

Currently the ceilometer-expirer doesn't delete expired AlarmChanges.
Remained AlarmChanges would be cause of wasted disk-space and slow response.
This patch aims to delete AlarmChanges.

This patch adds a new config option:
[database]
alarm_history_time_to_live = -1

Implements: blueprint delete-alarmhistory
DocImpact
Change-Id: Ib6bda6df720cf8514b621bfe13dd3acba941949f

subject: PXE/ISCSI: Call partx after partioning the disk
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-04-24 16:25:10.000000000', 'files': ['ironic/tests/test_disk_partitioner.py', 'etc/ironic/rootwrap.d/ironic-utils.filters', 'ironic/common/disk_partitioner.py', 'ironic/tests/drivers/test_deploy_utils.py'], 'message': "PXE/ISCSI: Call partx after partioning the disk

The _wait_for_disk_to_become_available function from
common/disk_partitioner.py calls fuser to check if the is not being held
by another process, but it doesn't actually check if the partitions of the
device is available after the disk is partitioned. This patch adds a call
to partx -u to make the kernel re-read the partition table of the device
and then list the partitions to verify if they are really available.

Change-Id: Iceee04af624666345eb464a100e51746790a547c
Closes-Bug: #1403887
Co-authored-by: Lucas Alvares Gomes <lucasagomes@gmail.com>
"}]
commit_message:
PXE/ISCSI: Call partx after partioning the disk

The _wait_for_disk_to_become_available function from
common/disk_partitioner.py calls fuser to check if the is not being held
by another process, but it doesn't actually check if the partitions of the
device is available after the disk is partitioned. This patch adds a call
to partx -u to make the kernel re-read the partition table of the device
and then list the partitions to verify if they are really available.

Change-Id: Iceee04af624666345eb464a100e51746790a547c
Closes-Bug: #1403887
Co-authored-by: Lucas Alvares Gomes <lucasagomes@gmail.com>

These tests will attempt CRUD operations on Secret resources, both
with and without (dummy) project ids, and always without valid tokens.
They should all return HTTP 401s. Fixed block comment formatting for
PEP8. Added tests to SecretsUnauthedTestCase class, with 'security'
and 'negative' tags for all tests. Refactored test names to be in line
with rest of Barbican functional tests, and now using behaviors instead
of client calls. Added tests to create and attempt CRUD operations on
real secrets, and with and without real project-id headers.

Change-Id: Iaae76c13dee795c9ff9f99dfdceb139141c0445a
"}]
commit_message:
Security tests for Secret resources

These tests will attempt CRUD operations on Secret resources, both
with and without (dummy) project ids, and always without valid tokens.
They should all return HTTP 401s. Fixed block comment formatting for
PEP8. Added tests to SecretsUnauthedTestCase class, with 'security'
and 'negative' tags for all tests. Refactored test names to be in line
with rest of Barbican functional tests, and now using behaviors instead
of client calls. Added tests to create and attempt CRUD operations on
real secrets, and with and without real project-id headers.

Change-Id: Iaae76c13dee795c9ff9f99dfdceb139141c0445a

commit_message:

This patch adds the following changes:

1. Section Upload and manage images: *OpenStack Virtual
Machine Image Guide* - removed visible tags **;
2. Changed Image Service to Image service (according to the
latest Conventions updates);
3. Section Upload Images:
a) Added all the parameters from the initial xml table,
b) fixed broken enumeration.

MySQL: change default MySQL collate to utf8_general_ci

which is the way documented in OpenStack [1] and already the default
in puppetlabs-mysql [2].

[1] http://goo.gl/GA5gyZ
[2] https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-mysql/blob/master/manifests/db.pp#L7

commit_message:
Disable and mark heartbeat as experimental

Due to some discovered issues since heartbeat is enabled by default.
Specially #1436788, that needs to fix the underlying library, too.
So, according to the discution here:
https://bugs.launchpad.net/oslo.messaging/+bug/1436769/comments/10

We decide to mark the implementation as experimental and disable it by default.

Related-bug: #1436788
Related-bug: #1436769
Change-Id: Ib7c55977f976bdbbc8df4ad5915e0433cbf84a17
(cherry picked from commit 287a4f56f45ed9cd40116a9e7b6e529f3382a925)

commit_message:
Remove ping check from basic scenario test

ICMP ping was a workaround to proof that a connection between
storage server and VM was working. Since it's now supporting actual
mount operations this is just optional. By default this check is
deactivated.

Change-Id: I0eba48abc4583b2d1a4d690c92137941463730c1
Partially-implements: blueprint scenario-tests

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-04-22 19:59:27.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/openstack/common/service.py'], 'message': "service child process normal SIGTERM exit

service.py had some code where the child process would catch the
SIGTERM from the parent just so it could exit with 1 status rather
than with an indication that it exited due to SIGTERM. When
shutting down the parent doesn't care in what way the child ended,
only that they're all gone, so this code is unnecessary.

Also, for some reason this caused the child to never exit while
there was an open connection from a client. Probably something
with eventlet and signal handling.

This is a cherry-pick of oslo-incubator commit
702bc569987854b602ef189655c201c348de84cb .

Change-Id: I87f3ca4da64fb8070e4d6c3876a2f1ce1a3ca71d
Closes-Bug: #1446583
"}]
commit_message:
service child process normal SIGTERM exit

service.py had some code where the child process would catch the
SIGTERM from the parent just so it could exit with 1 status rather
than with an indication that it exited due to SIGTERM. When
shutting down the parent doesn't care in what way the child ended,
only that they're all gone, so this code is unnecessary.

Also, for some reason this caused the child to never exit while
there was an open connection from a client. Probably something
with eventlet and signal handling.

This is a cherry-pick of oslo-incubator commit
702bc569987854b602ef189655c201c348de84cb .

Change-Id: I87f3ca4da64fb8070e4d6c3876a2f1ce1a3ca71d
Closes-Bug: #1446583

commit_message:
Improve iSCSI deployment logs

This patch just add some DEBUG and INFO logs for the iSCSI deployment
methodology, so that the operator knows what's the steps the ramdisk is
taken by looking at the conductor logs.

The patch add logs for Ironic when working with both supported ramdisks
DIB and IPA.

Change-Id: Iaee09643b03877a1a735b6019def47445bf3e16f

commit_message:
Set kernel and ramdisk ID for ironic nodes

Ironic has deprecated per-flavor ramdisk and kernel image IDs in favor
of setting them per-node. These parameters are optional to preserve
backward compatibility. For ease of use, the command line client takes
the kernel and ramdisk name and looks up the ID via glance. Also, they
are completely ignored on nova-bm since it does not have a per-node
setting for these ids.

Co-Authored-By: Steve Kowalik <steven@wedontsleep.org>

Change-Id: I702afe81038b6f962ce383edb58227a6015c2a75
Partial-Bug: #1401617

commit_message:
SELinux keepalived read denials

Custom policy to fix read denials seen on overcloud controller node.

Filed bug to upstream selinux-policy for a more permanent fix:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1187348

Change-Id: I51b6081642e5fb6c4df1bbaefaffc86cb69fc7ff

commit_message:
Fix deployment of unprovisioned node in perf tests

After merging I7405ba54d90f6bc986befb5d035b213e4c0f6a73 a bug appear
in performance tests - in one of the tests there was a try to run deploy
on nodes that was "unprovisioned". This fix simulates "provisioned" nodes.

Change-Id: If178ccc9597a2b159082d430f5744aa1220ab5e5
Closes-Bug: #1447949

commit_message:
Fix test_matchmaker_redis on Python 3

redis.smembers(str) returns a list of byte strings.

I missed test failures when I submited my patch to enable redis on
Python 3. I didn't notice that redis tests are skipped when no local
redis server is running.

Change-Id: Ib9ec4e05eb9abd51613f32c93118a1c76649798a

commit_message:
Fixes k8s deployment without Replication Controller

UpdatePod execution plan was using field from Pod
definition that was present in v1beta1 API but is no
longer used in v1beta3

commit_message:
testr requires python's gdbm

Debian/Ubuntu have *helpfully* removed gdbm from the base python
package and put it into another package, which is not dragged in by
installing python. Testr doesn't function without this.

We should ensure this always gets installed.

Depends-On: If48a8444b02ee1e105bc1d9ce78a0489ea0c405b

Change-Id: I85a0ffe5ee384e055e78fd3164c27d42a86bc39d

commit_message:
Relax pysendfile requirement

This explicit pinning seems to pre-date global-requirements.
After ~2 years, pysendfile released 2.0.1 in May and it is starting
to trickle into distros.  This changes the pinning to a >=2.0.0.

Change-Id: Ie44914e261ec439ebeaf246948971af30d90a388
